The Philip K. Dick Award is an American science fiction award given annually at Norwescon and sponsored by the Philadelphia Science Fiction Society and (since 2005) the Philip K. Dick Trust.
Named after science fiction and fantasy writer Philip K. Dick, it has been awarded since 1983, the year after his death.
It is awarded to the best original paperback published each year in the US.
